      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate, directly mapped to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1). Secondary QoIs include shear stress distribution and exposure time histograms. All QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision (worst-case hemolysis identification) and are computed from the same simulation outputs used in the validation study. Achieves Gradation 2."
